'''Adrian of Orléans''' (c. 755-d. before November 821) was a Frankish count. His sister [[Hildegard of Vinzgouw]] married [[Charlemagne]]; therefore, he was the emperor's brother-in-law and uncle to the next emperor, [[Louis the Pious]].

==Parentage==

He was the son of [[Gerold of Vinzgau]]{{sfn|Le Jan|2003|p=213}} and Emma of Alemannia.

==Family==

He married Waldrada,{{sfn|Le Jan|2003|p=213}} who may have been a daughter of Wilhelmid [[Adalhelm of Autun]], and had issue:

*[[Odo I, Count of Orleans]] (d. aft. 15 Feb 834),{{sfn|Le Jan|2003|p=213}} who married Engeltrude of Fézensac, daughter of Count [[Leuthard I of Paris]].
*[[Waldrada of Worms|Waldrada]] who married [[Robert III of Worms]] (d. 834), count of the Oberrheingau and the Wormsgau, father of [[Robert the Strong]].{{sfn|Le Jan|2003|p=213}}

