'''Petter Moen''' (14 February 1901 &ndash; 8 September 1944) was a Norwegian resistance member later known for his diaries.
During the [[occupation of Norway by Nazi Germany]] he edited the [[Underground media in German-occupied Europe|underground newspaper]] ''[[London-Nytt]]''.<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=|title=Petter Moen|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|first=Magne |last=Skodvin |authorlink=Magne Skodvin |editor=|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/Petter_Moen|language=Norwegian|accessdate=26 October 2009}}</ref> He was arrested in February 1944 when the German occupiers discovered several undercover newspapers.<ref name=kd-86>{{cite book |title=Krigens Dagbok |chapter=Det store pressekrakket |language=Norwegian |editor=[[Per Voksø|Voksø, Per]] |year=1984 |publisher=Det Beste |location=Oslo |isbn=82-7010-166-4 |page=400 }}</ref> Moen spent time imprisoned at [[Møllergata 19]], and he perished during transport to Germany with the ship [[SS Westfalen (1905)|SS ''Westfalen'']] in September 1944.<ref name=kl/> He is particularly known for his diary written with a pin on toilet paper during imprisonment.<ref name=nbl>{{cite encyclopedia|title=Petter Moen |encyclopedia=[[Norsk biografisk leksikon]] |publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|editor=[[Knut Helle|Helle, Knut]]| first=Ivar | last=Kraglund | url=http://www.snl.no/.nbl_biografi/Petter_Moen/utdypning|language=Norwegian|accessdate=26 October 2009}}</ref> The manuscript was found after the war and published in 1949 as ''Petter Moens dagbok'';<ref name=pmd>{{cite book |title=Petter Moens dagbok |publisher=Cappelen |year=1949 |location=Oslo |language=Norwegian }}</ref> it has been translated into several languages.<ref name=kl>{{cite encyclopedia |last=Moland |first=Arnfinn |authorlink=Arnfinn Moland |encyclopedia=[[Norsk krigsleksikon 1940-45]] |title=Moen, Petter |language=Norwegian |editor=[[Hans Fredrik Dahl|Dahl]] |editor2=[[Guri Hjeltnes|Hjeltnes]] |editor3=[[Berit Nøkleby|Nøkleby]] |editor4=[[Nils Johan Ringdal|Ringdal]] |editor5=[[Øystein Sørensen|Sørensen]] |url=http://mediabase1.uib.no/krigslex/m/m2.html#moen-petter |accessdate=26 October 2009 |year=1995 |publisher=Cappelen |location=Oslo |isbn=82-02-14138-9 |page=275 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140528010317/http://mediabase1.uib.no/krigslex/m/m2.html#moen-petter |archivedate=28 May 2014 |df= }}</ref>
