{{Use British English|date=March 2016}}
'''Robert Broadbridge''' (christened 22 June 1797 at [[Duncton]], [[Sussex]]; details of death unknown) was an English professional [[cricket]]er who played [[first-class cricket]] from 1822 to 1824.  He was mainly associated with [[Sussex county cricket teams|Sussex]] and made 4 known appearances in first-class matches, including 1 for [[The Bs]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/36/36448/36448 CricketArchive].  Retrieved on 4 August 2009.</ref>

